These are the materials prepared for the gpu class at northeastern university.

Three lectures are presented, covering the following topics.

[1] Lecture 1
  - shared memory
  - matrix multiplication optimization
  - bank conflicts 
  - other memory types


[2] Lecture 2
  - Pinned vs Non-pinned Memory
  - Dual copy engines
  - Unified Memory
 

[3] Lecture 3 (Optimization Tricks)
  - Profiling
  - Reduce branch divergence
  - Loop unrolling
  - Coalescing access
